.TH "batadv_mcast_want_rtr6_update" 9 "batadv_mcast_want_rtr6_update" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_mcast_want_rtr6_update \- update want-all-rtr6 counter and list
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" batadv_mcast_want_rtr6_update
.BI "(struct batadv_priv *bat_priv "  ","
.BI "struct batadv_orig_node *orig "  ","
.BI "u8 mcast_flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bat_priv" 12
the bat priv with all the soft interface information
.IP "orig" 12
the orig_node which multicast state might have changed of
.IP "mcast_flags" 12
flags indicating the new multicast state
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If the BATADV_MCAST_WANT_NO_RTR6 flag of this originator, orig, has
toggled then this method updates the counter and the list accordingly.

Caller needs to hold orig->mcast_handler_lock.
